WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Hitokakera no yuuki hirogete
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:53.430
Saisho wa minna BARABARA ni egaite ita chiheisen

10
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

11
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

12
00:00:53.740 --> 00:01:00.440
Ima nara hitotsu no bouenkyou de nozokeru

13
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

14
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

15
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:09.980
Kimi no KOKORO madowasu unmei no shoppai KONPASU

16
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

17
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Sakate ni kaji toru yo
Set a new course, turn the tables now

18
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! SHIGARAMI mo kako mo sutete
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

19
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Bokura nara sore demo waraeteru hazu
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

20
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

21
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:34.900
Yume wo kanaeru tame no namida naraba

22
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

23
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
Oshiku wa nai PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

24
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

25
00:01:56.180 --> 00:02:03.480
Fantasia

26
00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:16.320
Chestnut head! Monkeys!
Can you hear it?!

27
00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:25.250
The City of Gold...

28
00:02:25.630 --> 00:02:33.300
was right here!

29
00:02:38.970 --> 00:02:42.350
Son of a...! He actually did it!

30
00:02:43.230 --> 00:02:45.310
How beautiful...

31
00:02:45.690 --> 00:02:47.610
What a pretty sound!

32
00:02:47.610 --> 00:02:49.770
What is it, huh?!

33
00:02:52.990 --> 00:02:57.700
I had faith that this moment
would arrive one day...

34
00:02:58.530 --> 00:03:04.040
So this is the sound
that Noland heard.

35
00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:10.670
Suu...

36
00:03:10.670 --> 00:03:11.710
I wonder...

37
00:03:12.420 --> 00:03:14.800
if the vearth is singing...

38
00:03:19.930 --> 00:03:21.310
So gods...

39
00:03:22.140 --> 00:03:23.930
really exist?

40
00:03:24.430 --> 00:03:26.560
What a miracle!

41
00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:34.530
I had almost given up on hearing it
ring again after its 400-year silence.

42
00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:37.070
Great Warrior Kalgara...

43
00:03:37.860 --> 00:03:39.490
Can you hear...

44
00:03:40.700 --> 00:03:43.790
the echo of the Light of Shandora...?

45
00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:53.460
What's happening in this country?

46
00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:56.630
What is this tone?

47
00:03:56.630 --> 00:03:58.180
Could it be...?

48
00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:00.430
Is this the legendary sound?

49
00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:08.350
Can you hear it...

50
00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:11.020
Mont Blanc Noland?

51
00:04:11.610 --> 00:04:13.900
Sorry to have kept you
waiting so long.

52
00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:16.280
I truly hope...

53
00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:18.780
this reaches your descendants!

54
00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:30.670
You like the sound
of this bell too, huh?

55
00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:48.270
Boss! Th-That sound...

56
00:04:49.100 --> 00:04:50.310
Yeah!

57
00:04:50.310 --> 00:04:51.850
There's no doubt about it.

58
00:04:51.850 --> 00:04:55.900
Only one bell in the world
could echo so far!

59
00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:58.820
Now this is romance.

60
00:05:02.410 --> 00:05:03.280
From the sky...

61
00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:05.160
I'm all excited now...

62
00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:09.040
Y'know, there used to be
a tale about the monsters...

63
00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:11.370
that appear with
the cumuloimperator clouds.

64
00:05:11.750 --> 00:05:17.000
If a person were to stand high
in the sky against a strong sun...

65
00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.760
their figure would be projected
onto the dense mist far below.

66
00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:25.760
That shadow would loom
like a giant monster.

67
00:05:26.180 --> 00:05:30.230
So those monsters are really just
the shadows of people in the sky?!

68
00:05:30.230 --> 00:05:36.400
Then does that mean we've finally
confirmed that people live up there?!

69
00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:37.610
Yeah.

70
00:05:37.610 --> 00:05:42.410
I had dismissed that story
as nothing but pointless fantasy...

71
00:05:42.410 --> 00:05:45.240
but it seems like it was all true.

72
00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:50.830
I can clearly hear the ringing
of that massive golden bell.

73
00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:59.010
The City of Gold really does
exist in the sky!

